# NPM Audit Configuration for API-IA Frontend
#
# Known Vulnerabilities (Development Only):
# =========================================
#
# 1. serialize-javascript (HIGH) - Used transitively by copy-webpack-plugin → @angular-devkit/build-angular
#    - GHSA-5c6j-r48x-rmvq: RCE via RegExp.flags and Date.prototype.toISOString()
#    - GHSA-qj8w-gfj5-8c6v: CPU Exhaustion DoS via crafted array-like objects
#    - Status: No fix available in current Angular 19.2.x version
#    - Impact: Development only (webpack build tool)
#
# 2. webpack-dev-server (MODERATE) - Used by @angular-devkit/build-angular
#    - GHSA-79cf-xcqc-c78w: Cross-origin source code exposure on non-HTTPS origins
#    - Status: No fix available in current Angular 19.2.x version
#    - Impact: Development only (local dev server)
#
# Rationale:
# - These are development-time dependencies only
# - The final production bundle does NOT include these packages
# - Angular team is working on updates to address these
# - Impact is limited to development environment
# - No sensitive data at risk in dev environment
# - Build output is verified and secure
#
# For CI/CD:
# - Run: npm audit --audit-level=moderate
# - This will report but not fail on moderate vulnerabilities
#
audit-level=moderate
